---
const title = "Kurikomi";
const description =
  "A small software company in Uzbekistan, building open-source tools for developers and the people who use them.";
const canonical = "https://kurikomi.com/";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>{title} — open-source tools, made in Uzbekistan</title>
    <meta name="description" content={description} />
    <link rel="canonical" href={canonical} />
    <meta name="theme-color" content="#F7F3ED" />
    <meta name="color-scheme" content="light" />

    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <meta property="og:title" content={title} />
    <meta property="og:description" content={description} />
    <meta property="og:url" content={canonical} />
    <meta property="og:image" content="https://kurikomi.com/og.png" />
    <meta property="og:image:width" content="1200" />
    <meta property="og:image:height" content="630" />
    <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image" />
    <meta name="twitter:title" content={title} />
    <meta name="twitter:description" content={description} />
    <meta name="twitter:image" content="https://kurikomi.com/og.png" />

    <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.svg" type="image/svg+xml" />
    <link rel="alternate icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
    <link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="/apple-touch-icon.png" />

    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      rel="preload"
      as="style"
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Fraunces:opsz,wght@9..144,300;9..144,400;9..144,500&family=Inter:wght@400;500&display=swap"
    />
    <link
      rel="stylesheet"
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Fraunces:opsz,wght@9..144,300;9..144,400;9..144,500&family=Inter:wght@400;500&display=swap"
    />

    <style is:global>
      :root {
        --cream: #f7f3ed;
        --ink: #0e0e0e;
        --chestnut: #6b4423;
        --muted: #6b6b6b;
        --rule: rgba(14, 14, 14, 0.1);
        --serif: "Fraunces", Georgia, "Times New Roman", serif;
        --sans: "Inter", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", system-ui,
          sans-serif;
      }

      *,
      *::before,
      *::after {
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }

      html {
        -webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;
        text-size-adjust: 100%;
      }

      body {
        margin: 0;
        background: var(--cream);
        color: var(--ink);
        font-family: var(--sans);
        font-size: 1.0625rem;
        line-height: 1.7;
        font-feature-settings: "kern", "liga", "calt";
        font-variant-numeric: oldstyle-nums proportional-nums;
        -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
        -moz-osx-font-smoothing: grayscale;
      }

      a {
        color: inherit;
        text-decoration: underline;
        text-decoration-thickness: 1px;
        text-underline-offset: 0.2em;
        text-decoration-color: var(--rule);
        transition: text-decoration-color 0.2s ease, color 0.2s ease;
      }
      a:hover {
        color: var(--chestnut);
        text-decoration-color: var(--chestnut);
      }
      a:focus-visible {
        outline: 2px solid var(--chestnut);
        outline-offset: 3px;
        border-radius: 2px;
      }

      ::selection {
        background: var(--ink);
        color: var(--cream);
      }

      .page {
        max-width: 38rem;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 4rem 1.5rem 6rem;
      }

      @media (min-width: 768px) {
        .page {
          padding: 6rem 2rem 8rem;
        }
      }

      header {
        margin-bottom: 6rem;
      }

      .brand {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 0.875rem;
        margin-bottom: 5rem;
      }

      .brand svg {
        width: 32px;
        height: 32px;
        display: block;
      }

      .brand .wordmark {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-weight: 500;
        font-variation-settings: "opsz" 14;
        font-size: 1.125rem;
        letter-spacing: -0.005em;
        color: var(--ink);
      }

      h1 {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-weight: 400;
        font-variation-settings: "opsz" 96;
        font-size: clamp(1.875rem, 1.25rem + 2.8vw, 2.875rem);
        line-height: 1.13;
        letter-spacing: -0.018em;
        margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
        color: var(--ink);
        text-wrap: balance;
        font-feature-settings: "kern", "liga", "calt", "ss01";
      }

      .subhead {
        font-family: var(--sans);
        font-size: 1.0625rem;
        line-height: 1.6;
        color: var(--muted);
        margin: 0;
        max-width: 32rem;
        text-wrap: balance;
      }

      section {
        margin-bottom: 5rem;
      }

      section:last-of-type {
        margin-bottom: 4rem;
      }

      .eyebrow {
        font-family: var(--sans);
        font-size: 0.6875rem;
        font-weight: 500;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.16em;
        color: var(--muted);
        margin: 0 0 2rem;
      }

      p {
        margin: 0 0 1.4em;
        text-wrap: pretty;
      }

      p:last-child {
        margin-bottom: 0;
      }

      footer {
        border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
        padding-top: 2rem;
        font-size: 0.9375rem;
        color: var(--muted);
        line-height: 1.75;
      }

      footer p {
        margin: 0;
      }

      footer a {
        color: var(--ink);
      }

      .reveal {
        opacity: 0;
        transform: translateY(8px);
        animation: reveal 0.7s cubic-bezier(0.2, 0.6, 0.2, 1) forwards;
      }
      .r-1 { animation-delay: 0.05s; }
      .r-2 { animation-delay: 0.18s; }
      .r-3 { animation-delay: 0.28s; }
      .r-4 { animation-delay: 0.38s; }
      .r-5 { animation-delay: 0.48s; }
      .r-6 { animation-delay: 0.58s; }

      @keyframes reveal {
        to {
          opacity: 1;
          transform: none;
        }
      }

      @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
        .reveal {
          opacity: 1;
          transform: none;
          animation: none;
        }
        * {
          transition: none !important;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main class="page">
      <header>
        <div class="brand reveal r-1">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 128 128" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false">
            <path
              fill="#0E0E0E"
              d="M50.4 78.5a75.1 75.1 0 0 0-28.5 6.9l24.2-65.7c.7-2 1.9-3.2 3.4-3.2h29c1.5 0 2.7 1.2 3.4 3.2l24.2 65.7s-11.6-7-28.5-7L67 45.5c-.4-1.7-1.6-2.8-2.9-2.8-1.3 0-2.5 1.1-2.9 2.7L50.4 78.5Zm-1.1 28.2Zm-4.2-20.2c-2 6.6-.6 15.8 4.2 20.2a17.5 17.5 0 0 1 .2-.7 5.5 5.5 0 0 1 5.7-4.5c2.8.1 4.3 1.5 4.7 4.7.2 1.1.2 2.3.2 3.5v.4c0 2.7.7 5.2 2.2 7.4a13 13 0 0 0 5.7 4.9v-.3l-.2-.3c-1.8-5.6-.5-9.5 4.4-12.8l1.5-1a73 73 0 0 0 3.2-2.2 16 16 0 0 0 6.8-11.4c.3-2 .1-4-.6-6l-.8.6-1.6 1a37 37 0 0 1-22.4 2.7c-5-.7-9.7-2-13.2-6.2Z"
            />
          </svg>
          <span class="wordmark">Kurikomi</span>
        </div>

        <h1 class="reveal r-2">Kurikomi builds open-source tools for developers and the people who use them.</h1>
        <p class="subhead reveal r-3">A small software company in Uzbekistan, shipping freely and quietly.</p>
      </header>

      <section aria-labelledby="what" class="reveal r-4">
        <p id="what" class="eyebrow">What we make</p>
        <p>
          We make <a href="https://github-store.org">GitHub Store</a> — a cross-platform
          app store for GitHub releases. It runs on Android, Windows, macOS, and Linux.
          Twelve thousand five hundred people have starred it on GitHub; it has been
          used in a hundred and sixty-six countries.
        </p>
        <p>
          We make <a href="https://rikkaui.dev">RikkaUI</a> — a component library for
          Jetpack Compose, shaped by the same shadcn philosophy of code you own and
          can change. It does not lock you in.
        </p>
        <p>
          We make <a href="https://rikkaicons.dev">RikkaIcons</a> — a multi-style icon
          library for Android and Kotlin Multiplatform. We think it is the first of
          its kind in that ecosystem.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="why" class="reveal r-5">
        <p id="why" class="eyebrow">Why we exist</p>
        <p>
          The web is full of tools designed to grow rapidly, charge what the market
          will bear, and operate at the edge of what users will tolerate. We are not
          interested in building that.
        </p>
        <p>
          Kurikomi charges only for features whose delivery genuinely costs us money
          to run — storage, bandwidth, compute, continuous monitoring. Anything that
          runs on your device stays free, forever. The backend code is open source.
          You can self-host it.
        </p>
        <p>
          We will write more about the principle when there is something to charge
          for. For now, everything we ship is free.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="where" class="reveal r-6">
        <p id="where" class="eyebrow">Where we are</p>
        <p>
          Kurikomi was founded in 2026 in Bukhara, Uzbekistan. The team is one
          person, with help from family and a small group of users who care more
          than they have to.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you are building something open and you would like to talk, write to
          <a href="mailto:hello@kurikomi.com">hello@kurikomi.com</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <footer class="reveal r-6">
        <p>Kurikomi, Inc. &middot; Made in Uzbekistan</p>
        <p>
          <a href="https://github.com/kurikomi-labs">GitHub</a>
          &middot;
          <a href="mailto:hello@kurikomi.com">hello@kurikomi.com</a>
        </p>
        <p>&copy; 2026</p>
      </footer>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
